      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 193,
      "message": "You do not test the parameters at all. The implementation could be changed by substituting the values to something else, and the test would still pass. This Fake object should be more intelligent and actually reuse the passed values so they can be verified. Especially the errorCode and errorMessage. The Execution, for me at least, can be checked if it's the same reference as the one passed to the tested method.",
